-news%2Fmark-james-dead-songwriter-suspicious-minds-always-on-my-mind-elvis-1236035902%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Fmusic%2Fobituaries-people-news%2Fmark-james-dead-songwriter-suspicious-minds-always-on-my-mind-elvis-1236035902%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Fmusic%2Fobituaries-people-news%2Fmark-james-dead-songwriter-suspicious-minds-always-on-my-mind-elvis-1236035902%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20took%20over%20my%20family's%20collapsing%20business%20at%2027%2C%20made%20it%20profitable%2C%20and%20managed%20to%20sell%20it%20to%20a%20private%20equity%20group.%20Here%20are%20the%205%20principles%20I%20followed.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lauri%20Union%20took%20over%20her%20family's%20corrugated%20roofing%20company%20in%201992.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66557a9920abc1efe8fddc8a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELauri%20Union%20(R)%20took%20over%20her%20family's%20corrugated%20roofing%20company%20in%201992.%3Cp%3ELauri%20Union%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20graduating%2C%20Lauri%20Union%20took%20over%20her%20family's%20failing%20corrugated%20roofing%20business%20in%201992.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAs%20a%2027-year-old%20president%20and%20CEO%2C%20she%20managed%20to%20turn%20the%20company%20around%20and%20sell%20it%20years%20later.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUnion%20shared%20five%20principles%20she%20said%20helped%20her%20save%20the%20sinking%20business%20tied%20to%20her%20name.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20set%20out%20to%20take%20over%20the%20family%20business.%20My%20grandfather%20started%20a%20corrugated%20roofing%20company%20in%20North%20Carolina%20in%201946%2C%20and%20in%20the%201990s%20it%20was%20run%20by%20my%20parents%20while%20I%20finished%20business%20school.%20My%20plan%20after%20graduation%20was%20to%20live%20in%20Boston%20with%20my%20husband.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20my%20father%20fell%20ill%2C%20the%20company%20was%20in%20dire%20financial%20straits.%20My%20mother%2C%20who%20had%20no%20business%20leadership%20experience%2C%20stepped%20in%20and%20tried%20to%20turn%20things%20around%2C%20asking%20me%20for%20help.%20The%20business%20seemed%20hopeless%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20to%20help%20clear%20my%20parents'%20debts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20meant%20that%20in%201992%2C%20at%20age%2027%2C%20I%20became%20president%20and%20CEO%20of%20a%20sinking%20ship.%20Morale%20was%20low%2C%20and%20we'd%20just%20lost%20our%20biggest%20client%2C%20who%20contributed%2025%25%20of%20our%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20to%20overhaul%20the%20company%20and%20was%20able%20to%20turn%20it%20around%20to%20profitability%2C%20eventually%20growing%20our%20staff%20head%20count%20to%20350%20and%20selling%20to%20a%20private%20equity%20firm%20in%202004.%20Here%20are%20five%20lessons%20for%20running%20a%20family%20business%20that%20helped%20me%20get%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b5bbef7d-ff62-44c8-b7f0-ba233a0b634c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECheck%20your%20ego%20at%20the%20door%2C%20and%20be%20comfortable%20with%20saying%20'I%20don't%20know'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20often%20think%20being%20a%20leader%20means%20knowing%20what%20to%20do.%20When%20I%20joined%20my%20family's%20business%2C%20I%20arrived%20with%20prestigious%20academic%20degrees%20including%20an%20MBA%20from%20Harvard.%20But%20I%20only%20worked%20there%20before%20for%206%20weeks%20in%20one%20summer%2C%20so%20I%20knew%20very%20little%20about%20it.%20I%20also%20had%20never%20led%20any%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20quickly%20realized%20that%20the%20people%20who%20worked%20in%20the%20business%20had%20tremendous%20knowledge%20and%20that%20I%20could%20contribute%20far%20more%20by%20asking%20open-ended%20questions%20than%20by%20trying%20to%20take%20control%20and%20tell%20people%20what%20to%20do.%20I%20spent%20most%20of%20my%20first%20few%20months%20interviewing%20people%20in%20the%20company%20and%20figuring%20out%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20within%20a%20few%20short%20months%2C%20I%20had%20more%20knowledge%20about%20the%20business%20and%20industry%20than%20virtually%20anyone%20else%20in%20the%20company.%20While%20each%20person%20knew%20their%20role%2C%20I%20was%20the%20only%20one%20who%20had%20interviewed%20so%20many%20people%20that%20I%20had%20a%20broad%20perspective%20on%20the%20company.%20I%20envisioned%20it%20as%20everyone%20having%20their%20own%20pie%20slice%2C%20but%20my%20goal%20was%20to%20see%20the%20entire%20pie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c8338711-86fc-495d-afb6-6841a84f6667%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EStay%20close%20to%20your%20family%2C%20but%20don't%20let%20family%20emotions%20interfere%20with%20your%20decisions.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20with%20family%20can%20bring%20up%20strong%20emotions%2C%20like%20frustration%20when%20a%20parent%20tells%20you%20what%20to%20do%20in%20front%20of%20other%20employees%20you%20are%20trying%20to%20lead.%20Or%20a%20feeling%20of%20rejection%20when%20a%20parent%20doesn't%20recognize%20what%20you%20consider%20to%20be%20a%20great%20achievement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFamilies%20pass%20emotions%20between%20members%2C%20so%20negative%20emotions%20can%20spiral.%20Those%20negative%20emotions%20can%20lead%20people%20to%20make%20decisions%20that%20make%20them%20feel%20better%2C%20rather%20than%20decisions%20that%20work%20best%20for%20the%20business.%20And%20those%20negative%20emotions%20can%20seriously%20damage%20family%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBe%20aware%20of%20your%20emotions%20and%20empathetic%20to%20your%20family%2C%20but%20be%20willing%20to%20make%20decisions%20that%20achieve%20shared%20goals%2C%20even%20if%20they%20are%20hard.%20Spending%20personal%20time%20away%20from%20work%20with%20my%20mom%20also%20helped%20us%20to%20stay%20close%2C%20even%20if%20we%20might%20disagree%20about%20something%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221ac35795-deba-4f91-b8ad-9601f97f3839%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20easier%20to%20get%20employees%20on%20board%20with%20your%20family's%20values.%20Use%20that.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFamily%20businesses%20have%20a%20superpower%20in%20their%20ability%20to%20consistently%20lead%20through%20a%20set%20of%20values%20that%20employees%20and%20customers%20can%20relate%20to.%20That%20makes%20the%20work%20of%20running%20the%20business%20meaningful%20to%20you%20and%20to%20other%20stakeholders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20case%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20longtime%20employees%20remembered%20what%20my%20grandfather's%20company%20used%20to%20stand%20for%2C%20and%20were%20discouraged%20by%20many%20of%20the%20firm's%20more%20recent%20practices.%20Employees%20were%20lying%20to%20customers%2C%20and%20everyone%20behaved%20like%20they%20were%20on%20a%20losing%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20met%20one%20of%20the%20firm's%20retired%20former%20workers%2C%20he%20recalled%20how%20my%20grandfather%20insisted%20on%20not%20increasing%20roofing%20prices%20after%20Hurricane%20Hazel%20in%201954.%20That%20story%20spoke%20to%20me%2C%20so%20I%20shared%20it%20at%20a%20company%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20employees%20stood%20up%20and%20told%20similar%20stories.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20meeting%2C%20we%20agreed%20that%20whatever%20happened%2C%20we%20would%20always%20do%20the%20right%20thing%2C%20even%20if%20that%20meant%20lower%20profits.%20We%20would%20never%20lie%20to%20a%20customer%20and%20always%20admit%20if%20we%20couldn't%20deliver%20what%20a%20client%20wanted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20a%20turning%20point%20for%20the%20company.%20Our%20employees%20felt%20they%20could%20be%20authentic%2C%20and%20it%20guided%20the%20company%20going%20forward%20and%20contributed%20to%20our%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d9648bdc-34d6-4377-8a18-7142b9b55dad%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20be%20afraid%20to%20take%20the%20business%20in%20a%20new%20direction%20from%20what%20your%20parents%20did%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFamily%20businesses%20can%20be%20slow%20to%20change%20because%20holding%20on%20to%20traditions%20or%20long-term%20relationships%20with%20employees%20and%20customers%20is%20valuable.%20Parents%20leading%20a%20family%20business%20may%20expect%20their%20children%20to%20join%20and%20follow%20in%20their%20footsteps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20average%20business%20today%20only%20lasts%20around%2010%20years.%20Families%20that%20try%20to%20get%20the%20next%20generation%20to%20follow%20the%20mold%20are%20at%20risk.%20The%20next%20generation%20may%20not%20be%20fully%20engaged%2C%20and%20the%20business%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20times.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20advice%20is%20to%20find%20your%20own%20shoes%20and%20lead%20the%20business%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20case%2C%20what%20was%20obvious%20about%20my%20family%20company%20was%20that%20it%20was%20a%20not%20very%20good%20business%2C%20and%20poorly%20positioned%20in%20a%20declining%20market.%20Our%20customer%20base%20was%20shrinking%2C%20our%20equipment%20was%20old%2C%20and%20employees%20hadn't%20been%20given%20raises%20for%20five%20years.%20We%20had%20six%20facilities%20in%20multiple%20states%2C%20most%20piling%20up%20with%20old%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20took%20over%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20change%20the%20company's%20model%20entirely.%20Instead%20of%20delivering%20in%20bulk%20to%20lots%20of%20customers%20in%20a%20large%20area%2C%20we%20focused%20on%20a%20small%20area%20of%20clients%20and%20delivered%20smaller%20shipments%20quickly.%20Eventually%2C%20we%20had%20enough%20money%20to%20buy%20one%20new%20machine%2C%20and%20we%20built%20on%20that%20success%20from%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2233e60c4c-5762-4368-8303-91e8cf34c358%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20try%20to%20live%20up%20to%20someone%20else's%20leadership%20style.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20family%20businesses%2C%20leaders%20can%20shape%20their%20own%20leadership%20style.%20Understand%20how%20others%20have%20led%20the%20business%20in%20the%20past%2C%20but%20don't%20be%20limited%20by%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20a%20young%20woman%20running%20a%20business%20in%20a%20male-dominated%20construction%20materials%20business.%20All%20leaders%20in%20the%20business%2C%20not%20just%20positions%20like%20the%20CEO%2C%20were%20men.%20Many%20managers'%20approaches%20were%20more%20authoritarian%2C%20with%20harsh%20language%20and%20aggressive%20stances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wasn't%20comfortable%20with%20that%2C%20but%20it%20was%20my%20family's%20business%2C%20so%20I%20could%20experiment%20with%20different%20ways%20to%20lead.%20I%20tried%20to%20be%20more%20calm%20and%20curious.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinding%20my%20own%20leadership%20style%2C%20rather%20than%20trying%20to%20live%20up%20to%20someone%20else's%2C%20made%20me%20a%20more%20effective%20and%20genuine%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flauri-union-take-over-family-business-sell-private-equity-principles-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718235721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66557a9920abc1efe8fddc8a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flauri-union-take-over-family-business-sell-private-equity-principles-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Lauri%20Union%20became%20CEO%20of%20her%20family's%20multi-state%20business%20at%2027%2C%20and%20had%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20rebuild%20the%20failing%20business%20and%20make%20it%20profitable%20again.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40businessinsider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flauri-union-take-over-family-business-sell-private-equity-principles-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%2