c%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6669b8e2e079049018182611%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20avian%20influenza%20A(H5N1)%20virion%2C%20viewed%20through%20an%20electron%20microscope.%3Cp%3ECynthia%20Goldsmith%2C%20Jackie%20Katz%2FCDC%20via%20AP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20CDC%20analyzed%20a%20virus%20sample%20from%20the%20second%20US%20farmworker%20infected%2C%20they%20spotted%20a%20mutation%20in%20the%20virus's%20replication%20machinery%20%E2%80%94%20the%20way%20it%20gets%20inside%20its%20host's%20cells%20to%20make%20copies%20of%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20change%20%26quot%3Bassociated%20with%20viral%20adaptation%20to%20mammalian%20hosts%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CDC%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fflu%2Favianflu%2Fspotlights%2F2023-2024%2Fh5n1-technical-update-may-24-2024.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%20in%20May%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20statement%20also%20said%20that%20studies%20in%20mice%20indicate%20this%20type%20of%20genetic%20mutation%20in%20the%20virus%20is%20associated%20with%20more%20severe%20disease%20and%20enhanced%20viral%20replication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20make%20it%20a%20human%20virus%20yet%2C%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20than%20this%20one%20change%2C%20H5N1%20has%20mainly%20%26quot%3Bavian%20virus%20properties%20and%20not%20human%20virus%20properties%2C%26quot%3B%20Richard%20Webby%2C%20a%20virologist%20at%20St.%20Jude%20and%20director%20of%20the%20WHO%20Collaborating%20Centre%20for%20Studies%20on%20the%20Ecology%20of%20Influenza%20in%20Animals%20and%20Birds%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20the%20virus%20is%20better%20adapted%20to%20thrive%20and%20spread%20among%20birds%2C%20not%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20that%20could%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ddfee4b3-1706-4652-9418-5ae34679d762%5C%22%3EThe%20latest%20US%20case%20had%20a%20troubling%20cough%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20two%20farmworkers%20to%20test%20positive%20for%20H5N1%20in%20the%20US%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ftreatments%2Fpink-eye-treatment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epink%20eye%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20the%20third%20case%2C%20reported%20in%20Michigan%20in%20May%2C%20featured%20a%20cough%20and%20sore%20throat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20H5N1%20was%20in%20that%20worker's%20respiratory%20system%2C%20which%20is%20a%20scarier%20place%20to%20find%20a%20threatening%20virus%20than%20in%20our%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%20thing%2C%20it's%20easier%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-covid-positive-biden-statement-meadows-book-coughing-on-people-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espread%20a%20virus%20by%20coughing%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20sneezing%20than%20by%2C%20well%2C%20sharing%20eye%20fluid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222084%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20coughing%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61c3b0231f3fca0018a53192%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221439%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECoughing%20can%20spread%20respiratory%20infections%20such%20as%20the%20common%20cold%20or%20COVID-19.%3Cp%3EStock%20Photo%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%2C%20as%20far%20as%20scientists%20can%20tell%2C%20H5N1%20is%20still%20not%20adapted%20to%20humans%20enough%20to%20transmit%20between%20us.%20The%20CDC%20has%20reported%20no%20evidence%20that%20the%20coughing%20farmworker%20spread%20the%20virus%20to%20anyone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20H5N1%20can't%20mutate%20to%20achieve%20human-to-human%20transmission%20%E2%80%94%20which%20brings%20us%20to%20the%20second%20unfortunate%20reality%20of%20this%20farmworker's%20respiratory%20infection.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompared%20to%20the%20eyes%2C%20human%20lungs%20are%20a%20more%20convenient%20place%20for%20an%20avian%20virus%20to%20get%20more%20mammalian%2C%20according%20to%20Webby.%20In%20the%20lungs%2C%20the%20virus%20is%20exposed%20to%20more%20of%20the%20cell%20receptors%20that%20a%20mammalian%20virus%20would%20bind%20to%2C%20giving%20H5N1%20more%20opportunity%20to%20mutate%20and%20start%20grabbing%20onto%20those%20receptors%20%E2%80%94%20thereby%20becoming%20better%20adapted%20to%20infecting%20and%20spreading%20between%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20experts%20fear%20the%20USDA%20and%20CDC%20aren't%20monitoring%20cattle%20and%20farmworkers%20closely%20enough%20to%20catch%20concerning%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emutations%20early%2C%20and%20that%20other%20human%20cases%20may%20be%20going%20undetected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22blue%20gloved%20hands%20in%20a%20white%20lab%20coat%20hold%20a%20large%20syringe%20and%20a%20lab%20tube%20of%20fluid%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F665e33401cd3b1779042e831%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETalita%20de%20Lima%20Freitas%2C%20federal%20agricultural%20inspector%2C%20works%20on%20a%20sample%20to%20test%20for%20avian%20influenza%20virus%20at%20the%20Reference%20Laboratory%20of%20the%20World%20Organization%20for%20Animal%20Health%20in%20Campinas%2C%20Brazil.%3Cp%3EAmanda%20Perobelli%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20there's%20enough%20of%20a%20threat%20here%20to%20be%20very%20alert%20so%20that%20we%20have%20a%20surveillance%20system%20in%20place%20that%2C%20as%20soon%20as%20this%20happens%2C%20we%20can%20find%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Dye%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22048d06aa-b91d-4421-b98b-5ae259b70f87%5C%22%3EVaccines%20are%20in%20the%20works%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%20bird%20flu%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faugust-flu-vs-covid-infection-rate-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20COVID-19%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Scientists%20have%20been%20tracking%20this%20virus%20and%20its%20entire%20viral%20family%20tree%2C%20watching%20for%20any%20sign%20of%20a%20growing%20threat%20to%20humans%2C%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20the%20key%20elements%20of%20a%20vaccine%20are%20already%20on%20standby.%20The%20US%20is%20beginning%20to%20manufacture%20millions%20of%20vaccines%20using%20%26quot%3Bcandidate%20vaccine%20viruses%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0weakened%20influenza%20viruses%20%E2%80%94%20that%20the%20CDC%20has%20developed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22how%20does%20the%20flu%20shot%20work%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f89e783d260780019341ea0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIf%20H5N1%20becomes%20a%20threat%20to%20humans%2C%20it%20could%20be%20part%20of%20your%20seasonal%20flu%20shot.%3Cp%3EMarko%20Geber%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20candidates%20are%20not%20necessarily%20perfect%20matches%20to%20H5N1%2C%20and%20the%20vaccines'%20use%20of%20eggs%20may%20be%20a%20manufacturing%20roadblock%20if%20bird%20flu%20is%20sweeping%20the%20chicken%20population%2C%20they%20may%20provide%20some%20immunity%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20human%20outbreak.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20scientists%20now%20have%20proven%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmrna-vaccine-pfizer-moderna-coronavirus-2020-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EmRNA%20vaccine%20technology%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20ready.%20Vaccines%20that%20use%20mRNA%2C%20of%20which%20the%20COVID-19%20vaccines%20were%20the%20first%20approved%20for%20use%2C%20are%20more%20flexible%20and%20faster%20to%20develop%20than%20traditional%20vaccines%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20don't%20require%20eggs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22white%20shiny%20eggs%20on%20a%20machine%20c