%3A%22mmcfalljohnsen%40businessinsider.com%20(Morgan%20McFall-Johnsen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A38%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fh5n1-bird-flu-virus-experts-concerned-human-outbreak-spread-possible-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Here's%20where%20Biden%20and%20Trump%20stand%20on%20immigration%20in%20the%202024%20race%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224853%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US-Mexico%20border%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63a9c12946a5550018b7ef9b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223235%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMigrants%20line%20up%20along%20the%20US-Mexico%20border%20fence%20to%20apply%20for%20asylum%20in%20the%20United%20States%20on%20December%2021%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Moore%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EImmigration%20is%20one%20of%20the%20thorniest%20public%20policy%20issues%20and%20one%20that%20will%20define%20the%202024%20election.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBiden%20has%20had%20to%20pivot%20on%20some%20of%20his%20border%20policies%20after%20running%20against%20Trump's%20efforts%20in%202020.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Trump%20is%20seeking%20to%20run%20heavily%20on%20immigration%20this%20year%2C%20similar%20to%20his%202016%20campaign.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EVery%20few%20issues%20animate%20Americans%20more%20than%20immigration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20under%20the%20presidencies%20of%20both%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20divisions%20over%20the%20issue%20have%20only%20sharpened%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%202016%20presidential%20campaign%20was%20defined%20by%20his%20hard-line%20views%20on%20immigration%3A%20arguing%20for%20a%20wall%20at%20the%20US-Mexico%20border%20and%20insisting%20that%20Mexico%20pay%20for%20said%20barrier%2C%20pushing%20for%20the%20deportations%20of%20millions%20of%20undocumented%20immigrants%2C%20and%20calling%20for%20a%20temporary%20ban%20on%20Muslims%20entering%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20in%20office%2C%20Trump%20sought%20to%20execute%20his%20broad%20vision.%20His%20administration%20constructed%20455%20miles%20of%20fencing%20along%20the%20southern%20border%2C%20but%20much%20of%20the%20wall%20simply%20replaced%20anti-vehicle%20barriers%20with%20taller%20steel%20bars.%20And%20despite%20Trump's%20rhetoric%20on%20ramping%20up%20deportations%2C%20the%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F12%2F11%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Ftrump-deportations-undocumented-immigrants.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindividuals%20who%20were%20removed%20from%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%20declined%20from%20October%202018%20to%20September%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden%20in%20the%202020%20election%20strongly%20denounced%20Trump's%20immigration%20policies%2C%20voicing%20his%20opposition%20to%20a%20border%20wall%2C%20blasting%20the%20GOP%20administration's%20family%20separation%20policy%2C%20and%20promising%20a%20more%20humane%20approach%20toward%20migrants%20at%20the%20southern%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20since%20Biden%20took%20office%2C%20an%20explosion%20in%20border%20apprehensions%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20scores%20of%20migrants%20arriving%20in%20Democratic-led%20cities%20like%20Chicago%20and%20New%20York%20%E2%80%94%20has%20became%20a%20political%20liability%2C%20with%20voters%20giving%20him%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-immigration-us-mexico-border-disapproval-poll-abbott-adams-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elow%20marks%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20look%20at%20Biden%20and%20Trump's%20positions%20on%20immigration%2C%20one%20of%20the%20defining%20issues%20of%20the%20November%20election%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2224b5896f-83f5-4b23-b6a1-42591ce94e58%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20Joe%20Biden%20stands%20on%20immigration%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EImmigration%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20trickiest%20policy%20areas%20for%20Biden%2C%20as%20he%20came%20into%20office%20seeking%20to%20reverse%20many%20Trump-era%20policies%20but%20has%20instead%20often%20found%20himself%20on%20the%20defensive%20on%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepublicans%20across%20the%20country%20have%20routinely%20excoriated%20Biden%20over%20border%20security%20since%20taking%20office%2C%20pointing%20their%20fingers%20at%20him%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2024%2F02%2F15%2Fmigrant-encounters-at-the-us-mexico-border-hit-a-record-high-at-the-end-of-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecord%20levels%20of%20apprehensions%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20border.%20In%20February%2C%20the%20GOP-controlled%20House%20of%20Representatives%20impeached%20Homeland%20Security%20Secretary%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falejandro-mayorkas-impeachment-trial-what-happens-immigration-biden-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlejandro%20Mayorkas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20contending%20that%20he%20had%20not%20enforced%20the%20country's%20immigration%20laws.%20(The%20Democratic-led%20Senate%20subsequently%20squashed%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falejandro-mayorkas-impeachment-trial-killed-murkowski-present-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpeachment%20charges%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20Mayorkas.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%20GOP%20Gov.%20Greg%20Abbott%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years%20has%20pushed%20back%20against%20what%20he%20said%20is%20Biden's%20lack%20of%20border%20security%20by%20sending%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20migrants%20to%20Chicago%20and%20New%20York.%20And%20it's%20created%20a%20difficult%20situation%20for%20Democratic%20officials%20like%20New%20York%20City%20Mayor%20Eric%20Adams%2C%20who%20has%20had%20to%20tackle%20budgetary%20challenges%20in%20housing%20migrants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden%20this%20year%20pushed%20for%20the%20passage%20of%20a%20Senate-crafted%20bipartisan%20bill%2C%20which%20would%20have%20overhauled%20the%20US%20asylum%20system%2C%20among%20other%20measures%20intended%20to%20strengthen%20security%20at%20the%20border.%20The%20bill%20seemingly%20put%20the%20president%20on%20the%20offensive%20on%20the%20issue%2C%20as%20he%20challenged%20congressional%20Republicans%20to%20back%20to%20proposal%20to%20get%20a%20handle%20on%20immigration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-conservatives-border-security-immigration-bill-biden-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESenate%20Republicans%3C%2Fa%3E%20overwhelmingly%20voted%20against%20the%20bill%20after%20Trump%20pressed%20them%20to%20tank%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden%20last%20week%20signed%20an%20executive%20order%20that%20restricts%20asylum%20protections%20%E2%80%94%20to%20the%20frustration%20of%20immigration%20advocates%20%E2%80%94%20for%20migrants%20if%20there%20are%20more%20than%202%2C500%20unauthorized%20daily%20border%20crossings%20over%20a%20seven-day%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229353db08-b724-47e9-a49c-27a8bdbcf8ca%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20Donald%20Trump%20stands%20on%20immigration%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20staked%20much%20of%20his%202024%20campaign%20on%20Biden's%20vulnerabilities%20on%20immigration%20among%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2024%2F04%2F14%2Fus%2Felections%2Ftimes-siena-poll-registered-voter-crosstabs.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Times%2FSiena%20College%20poll%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20in%20April%2C%2050%25%20of%20registered%20voters%20approved%20of%20Trump's%20handling%20of%20the%20issue%20while%20he%20was%20in%20office.%20Meanwhile%2C%20only%2032%25%20of%20registered%20voters%20approved%20of%20Biden's%20handling%20of%20immigration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20president%20was%20instrumental%20in%20tanking%20this%20year's%20bipart