-putin-politics-motive-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eobjectives%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20war%20include%20the%20%26quot%3Bdemilitarization%20and%20de-Nazification%20of%20Ukraine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Azov%20Brigade%20has%20claimed%20that%20it%20has%20evolved%20from%20its%20problematic%20past%20and%20that%20its%20leadership%20has%20changed%20since%20its%20inception.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20response%20to%20the%20decision%20on%20Instagram%2C%20the%20unit%20wrote%20that%20%26quot%3Bobtaining%20Western%20weapons%20and%20training%20from%20the%20United%20States%20will%20not%20only%20increase%20the%20combat%20ability%20of%20Azov%2C%20but%20most%20importantly%2C%20contribute%20to%20the%20preservation%20of%20the%20lives%20and%20the%20health%20of%20personnel.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20new%20page%20in%20our%20unit's%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20brigade%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3BAzov%20is%20becoming%20even%20more%20powerful%2C%20even%20more%20professional%20and%20even%20more%20dangerous%20for%20occupiers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20brigade%20is%20closely%20associated%20with%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraines-high-profile-azov-brigade-rebuilt-to-fight-in-donetsk-forests-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esignificant%2C%20albeit%20costly%2C%20defense%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Mariupol%20in%202022%20at%20the%20start%20of%20Russia's%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20where%20it%20was%20eventually%20forced%20to%20surrender%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmariupol-ukraine-soldiers-injured-killed-russian-captivity-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efight%20from%20the%20Azovstal%20steel%20mill%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20unit's%20soldiers%20have%20been%20celebrated%20as%20heroes%20and%20symbol%20of%20Ukrainian%20resistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsi