%3Cp%3EYasin%20Ozturk%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3B%20Chelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20held%20interest%20rates%20steady%20in%20its%20latest%20decision%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIts%20Summary%20of%20Economic%20Projections%20also%20penciled%20in%20just%20one%20interest%20rate%20cut%20for%202024.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStill%2C%20Powell%20cautioned%20that%20could%20change%20and%20left%20the%20door%20open%20for%20a%20rate%20cut%20in%20September.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20odds%20of%20an%20interest%20rate%20cut%20this%20year%20just%20got%20slimmer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2012%2C%20the%20Federal%20Open%20Market%20Committee%20announced%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-interest-rates-decision-june-no-rate-cuts-inflation-powell-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit%20would%20hold%20interest%20rates%20steady%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20the%20nation's%20central%20bank%20continues%20to%20work%20to%20lower%20inflation%20to%20its%202%25%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20alongside%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20interest%20rate%20decision%2C%20the%20FOMC%20also%20released%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Fmonetarypolicy%2Ffiles%2Ffomcprojtabl20240612.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESummary%20of%20Economic%20Projections%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20committee%20now%20has%20just%20one%20interest%20rate%20cut%20penciled%20in%20for%202024%2C%20with%20further%20cuts%20expected%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20said%20during%20the%20Wednesday%20press%20conference%20that%20when%20looking%20at%20the%20FOMC's%20projections%2C%20they%20should%20be%20viewed%20as%20just%20that%3A%20projections.%20There's%20still%20time%20for%20them%20to%20change%20based%20on%20upcoming%20economic%20data%2C%20he%20said%2C%20and%20it's%20%26quot%3Bplausible%26quot%3B%20that%20a%20rate%20cut%20could%20happen%20as%20soon%20as%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20gain%20further%20confidence.%20Certainly%2C%20more%20good%20inflation%20readings%20will%20help%20with%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20be%20the%20totality%20of%20the%20data%2C%20what's%20happening%20in%20the%20labor%20market%2C%20what's%20happening%20with%20the%20balance%20of%20risks%2C%20what's%20happening%20with%20the%20forecast%2C%20what's%20happening%20with%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BYou%20look%20at%20all%20of%20that%2C%20and%20you%20ask%2C%20'Are%20we%20confident%3F%20Have%20we%20reached%20an%20appropriate%20level%20of%20confidence%20that%20inflation%20is%20moving%20down%20sustainably%20to%202%25%2C%20or%20alternatively%2C%20do%20we%20see%20really%20unexpected%20signs%20of%20weakness%20in%20the%20labor%20market%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Consumer%20Price%20Index%2C%20which%20measures%20inflation%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcpi-inflation-may-prices-rent-gas-fed-interest-rates-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erose%203.3%25%20year%20over%20year%20in%20May%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20slight%20decrease%20from%20April's%203.4%25%20reading%2C%20showing%20the%20economy%20is%20headed%20in%20the%20right%20direction.%20While%20Powell%20said%20the%20latest%20reading%20is%20a%20positive%20sign%2C%20it's%20not%20sufficient%20to%20allow%20the%20Fed%20to%20loosen%20its%20restrictive%20monetary%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20some%20Democratic%20lawmakers%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-when-will-fed-lower-rates-inflation-fomc-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eurged%20Powell%20to%20cut%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20sooner%20rather%20than%20later%2C%20given%20the%20financial%20strains%20Americans%20continue%20to%20face%20under%20high%20inflation.%20Powell%20acknowledged%20those%20pains%20but%20reiterated%20t