5C%22%3Eforeign%20policy%20arena%3C%2Fa%3E%20perish%20at%20the%20altar%20of%20coalition%20politics%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECollective%20wisdom%20suggests%20that%20despite%20a%20reduced%20mandate%2C%20India's%20foreign%20policy%20pursuit%20under%20Modi%203.0%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20affected.%20There%20is%20unanimity%20among%20politicians%20and%20pundits%20that%20the%20Modi%20government's%20mantra%20of%20'strategic%20consensus'%20and%20pursuit%20of%20multilateralism%20will%20continue%20to%20drive%20India%20towards%20becoming%20a%20global%20force%20as%20well%20as%20the%20world's%20third-largest%20economy%20(after%20the%20US%20and%20China)%20by%202027.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fwhat-will-add-heft-to-india-s-foreign-policy-801732%5C%22%3EWatch%20%7C%C2%A0What%20Will%20Add%20Heft%20To%20India's%20Foreign%20Policy%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20general%20consensus%20appears%20to%20be%20that%20Modi's%20foreign%20policy%20has%20already%20catapulted%20India%20onto%20the%20global%20stage.%20His%20actions%20have%20so%20far%20reflected%20a%20nuanced%20approach%20to%20maintaining%20an%20independent%20foreign%20policy%20that%20is%20in%20India's%20national%20interest.%20India%20may%20not%20yet%20be%20a%20great%20power%2C%20but%20is%20an%20emerging%20great%20power%2C%20as%20American%20political%20scientist%20John%20Mearsheimer%20recently%20suggested.%20In%20Modi's%20third%20term%2C%20India%20will%20certainly%20strive%20to%20go%20beyond%20an%20emerging%20great%20power%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20new%20reality%20of%20a%20coalition%20government%20is%20unlikely%20to%20undermine%20Modi's%20foreign%20policy%20goals%2C%20will%20it%20be%20smooth%20sailing%20for%20him%20from%20now%20onwards%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Challenges%20To%20Continue%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20Modi's%20last%20term%2C%20India%20had%20faced%20all%20kinds%20of%20pressure%20to%20become%20a%20formal%20US%20ally.%20But%20he%20commendably%20dodged%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpm-modi-in-us-pm-modi-lands-in-washington-will-hold-bilateral-talks-with-us-president-joe-biden-4141811%5C%22%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden's%20charm%20offensive%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Biden%20extended%20Modi%20a%20state%20visit%2C%20laced%20with%20a%20hero's%20welcome%20at%20the%20White%20House.%20It%20was%20one%20of%20the%20best%20moments%20of%20Modi's%20long%20political%20career%2C%20but%20instead%20of%20treating%20it%20as%20a%20personal%20triumph%20(remember%20he%20was%20denied%20entry%20by%20the%20US%20for%20years%20following%20the%20Gujarat%20violence%20in%202002%3F)%2C%20he%20saw%20it%20as%20a%20recognition%20for%20a%20rising%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi-Jaishankar%20partnership%20has%20stood%20firm%20on%20avoiding%20strict%20alliances%20with%20any%20major%20power.%20Instead%2C%20the%20duo%20has%20tried%20to%20balance%20relations%20among%20competing%20global%20powers%2C%20which%20can%20be%20observed%20in%20India's%20interactions%20with%20the%20US%2C%20Russia%20and%20China%2C%20as%20well%20as%20its%20balancing%20act%20between%20Israel%20and%20Middle%20Eastern%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20coming%20years%2C%20the%20challenges%20are%20going%20to%20become%20even%20bigger%20for%20the%20Modi%20government%20because%20the%20rise%20of%20China%20and%20a%20resurgent%20Russia%20are%20expected%20to%20continue%20to%20undermine%20the%20US-dominated%20liberal%20global%20order.%20The%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20has%20dragged%20on%20with%20no%20end%20in%20sight%2C%20and%20it%20is%20thus%20that%20the%20US%20is%20desperate%20to%20bring%20powers%20like%20India%20into%20its%20orbit%20of%20influence.%20If%20India%20were%20to%20become%20a%20formal%20US%20ally%2C%20it%20would%20be%20a%20huge%20shot%20in%20the%20arm%20for%20President%20Biden.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20it's%20obvious%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpm-modi-dials-putin-after-his-big-win-says-agreed-to-work-together-to-deepen-india-russia-ties-5276069%5C%22%3EPresident%20Putin%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20not%20like%20to%20lose%20an%20old%2C%20trusted%20friend%20in%20India%2C%20which%20relies%20heavily%20on%20him%20for%20its%20defence%20and%20energy%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20India%20Become%20A%20Formal%20US%20Ally%20Under%20Modi%203.0%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20academics%2C%20policymakers%20and%20analysts%20in%20the%20US%20continue%20to%20forcefully%20argue%20that%20becoming%20a%20formal%20US%20ally%20is%20more%20beneficial%20for%20India%20and%20that%20it'll%20help%20it%20achieve%20its%20goal%20of%20becoming%20a%20great%20global%20power.%20Many%20in%20India%20also%20believe%20it's%20in%20the%20country's%20national%20interest%20to%20join%20hands%20with%20the%20most%20powerful%20country%20on%20the%20planet.%20So%2C%20if%20it%20is%20indeed%20in%20India's%20national%20interest%2C%20why%20not%3F%20After%20all%2C%20India%20and%20the%20US%20are%20already%20part%20of%20the%20Quad%20grouping%2C%20along%20with%20Japan%20and%20Australia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20doubt%20the%20argument%20in%20favour%20of%20an%20India-US%20alliance%20is%20very%20powerful%20and%20loaded%20with%20benefits.%20%C2%A0India%20is%20faced%20with%20China's%20growing%20economic%20and%20military%20ambitions.%20So%2C%20could%20Modi%20feel%20compelled%20to%20enter%20a%20comprehensive%20agreement%20with%20the%20US%20and%20get%20more%20rewarding%20economic%20cooperation%20and%20an%20umbrella%20security%20protection%20against%20any%20future%20Chinese%20aggression%3F%20Given%20the%20recent%20incidents%20of%20border%20skirmishes%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20China%20is%20an%20immediate%20neighbour%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwilling-to-work-with-india-chinese-premier-li-qiang-congratulates-pm-modi-on-3rd-term-5868749%5C%22%3EIndia%20faces%20a%20bigger%20security%20threat%20from%20China%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20any%20other%20of%20its%20neighbours.%20Therefore%2C%20ostensibly%2C%20it%20makes%20sense%20to%20come%20under%20the%20US%20security%20cover.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20supporters%20of%20such%20an%20argument%20say%20that%20India%20needs%20investments%2C%20technology%2C%20and%20semiconductor%20chips%20for%20its%20industries.%20It%20also%20needs%20advanced%20weapons%20for%20its%20military.%20They%20believe%20the%20US%20can%20also%20help%20India%20become%20a%20permanent%20member%20of%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council.%20Most%20of%20all%2C%20they%20say%20that%20both%20countries%20share%20democratic%20values.%20They%20say%20if%20India%20were%20to%20become%20a%20US%20ally%2C%20it%20stands%20to%20gain%20much%20more%20from%20the%20alliance%20than%20the%20US%20does.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20also%20argue%20the%20alliance%20could%20be%20on%20the%20lines%20of%20NATO.%20The%20security%20relationship%20between%20the%20US%20and%20the%20European%20Union%20is%20anchored%20in%20NATO%2C%20established%20in%201949%20to%20protect%20Europe%20against%20the%20Communist%20Soviet%20Union.%20This%20military%20alliance%20not%20only%20ensures%20the%20defence%20of%20Europe%20but%20also%20fosters%20a%20close%20political%20relationship%20between%20the%20US%20and%20EU%20member%20states.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20return%2C%20the%20EU%20countries%20support%20US%20positions%20in%20global%20affairs.%20That's%20why%20the%20EU%20supported%20the%20American%20invasion%20of%20Iraq%20and%20they%20supported%20Israel%20without%20questioning%20much%20of%20its%20action%20in%20Gaza.%20In%20effect%2C%20many%20EU%20member%20countries%20have%20to%20exercise%20with%20caution%20their%20independent%20foreign%20policy%2C%20especially%20over%20an%20issue%20in%20which%20the%20US%20has%20a%20strategic%20interest.%20They%20have%20to%20toe%20the%20American%20line.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20who%20are%20not%20in%20favour%20of%20India%20becoming%20a%20US%20ally%20say%20that%20if%20India%20goes%20that%20way%2C%20it%20will%20have%20to%20sacrifice%20its%20foreign%20policy%20autonomy%2C%20and%20that%20is%20non-negotiable%20for%20the%20Modi-Jaishankar%20duo.%20For%20instance%2C%20if%20India%20had%20been%20a%20US%20ally%20in%202003%2C%20it%20would%20have%20had%20to%20make%20a%20hard%20choice%20between%20supporting%20the%20US%20invasion%20of%20Iraq%20and%20standing%20firm%20in%20solidarity%20with%20an%20old%20Arab%20friend.%20The%20Philippines%20and%20Thailand%20are%20US%20allies%20in%20East%20Asia.%20But%20has%20that%20helped%20them%20allay%20their%20China%20concerns%3F%20South%20Korea%20is%20an%20American%20ally%2C%20but%20its%20citizens%20spend%20sleepless%20nights%20whenever%20tensions%20with%20North%20Korea%20escalate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERooted%20In%20Reality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20India%20collaborates%20fully%20with%20the%20US%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20managing%20China's%20rapid%20rise%20as%20a%20global%20power.%20But%20here%20again%2C%20India's%20policy%20on%20China%20is%20primarily%20based%20on%20its%20own%20ground%20reality.%20The%20Galwan%20Valley%20clash%20has%20severely%20strained%20relations%20between%20India%20and%20China%20even%20though%20bilateral%20trade%20continues%20to%20boom.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20Russia%20has%20been%20India's%20all-weather%20friend%20and%20often%20does%20not%20appear%20to%20be%20wanting%20anything%20in%20return%20for%20its%20deep%20commitment%20to%20India.%20The%20US%20and%20other%20Western%20powers%20are%20wary%20of%20India's%20close%20ties%20with%20Russia.%20They%20have%20repeatedly%20asked%20India%20to%20condemn%20Russia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20Modi's%20Gulf%20policy%2C%20his%20engagements%20with%20the%20Gulf%20countries%20and%20West%20Asia%20have%20been%20a%20big%20success.%20On%20the%20Israel-Gaza%20issue%2C%20one%20expects%20India's%20strategic%20autonomy%20to%20continue.%20India's%20ties%20with%20Israel%20have%20grown%20stronger%20under%20Modi%2C%20with%20increased%20cooperation%20in%20defence%2C%20technology%2C%20and%20agriculture.%20They%20will%20become%20even%20stronger%20in%20the%20near%20future.%20Simultaneously%2C%20India%20has%20maintained%20strong%20ties%20with%20Arab%20countries%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20Gulf%2C%20which%20are%20crucial%20for%20energy%20security%20and%20the%20large%20Indian%20expatriate%20population.%20The%20West%20views%20India's%20balancing%20act%20positively%2C%20recognising%20the%20strategic%20importance%20of%20maintaining%20relations%20with%20both%20Israel%20and%20the%20Arab%20world.%20This%20balance%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20testament%20to%20India's%20diplomatic%20finesse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20policymakers%20believe%20that%20if%20India%20truly%20harbours%20the%20ambition%20of%20becoming%20a%20global%20power%2C%20it%20cannot%20remain%20a%20mute%20spectator%20in%20times%20of%20big%20global%20crises.%20For%20example%2C%20when%20the%20US%20under%20President%20Trump%20lost%20the%20trust%20of%20the%20Palestinians%20as%20a%20neutral%20mediator%2C%20some%20argued%20that%20it%20was%20an%20opportunity%20for%20India%20to%20offer%20its%20mediation%20and%20try%20to%20bring%20the%20Palestinians%20and%20Israel%20onto%20the%20negotiating%20table.%20After%20all%2C%20India%20enjoys%20immense%20goodwill%20among%20both%20the%20Israelis%20and%20the%20Palestinians.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20now%20give%20the%20example%20of%20China%2C%20which%20successfully%20brought%20together%20sworn%20enemies%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20Iran%20and%20earned%20the%20right%20to%20be%20a%20serious%20mediator.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20possible%20we%20may%20see%20a%20more%20assertive%20foreign%20policy%20in%20Modi's%20third%20term%2C%20in%20which%20India's%20stance%20on%20big%20global%20issues%20will%20be%20better%20articulated.%20But%20to%20expect%20India%20to%20mediate%20between%20warring%20parties%20may%20still%20be%20a%20step%