7B%22title%22%3A%22Merchant%20ship%20hit%20by%20small%20vessel%20in%20Red%20Sea%2C%20UKMTO%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718189000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-110939888%2Cimgsize-986280.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fmerchant-ship-hit-by-small-vessel-in-red-sea-ukmto-says%2Farticleshow%2F110939901.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F110939901.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EA%20merchant%20ship%20encountered%20an%20incident%20in%20the%20Red%20Sea%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20according%20to%20United%20Kingdom%20Maritime%20Trade%20Operations%20(UKMTO).%20The%20vessel%20was%20hit%20by%20a%20small%20craft.%20Two%20maritime%20sources%2C%20speaking%20anonymously%2C%20confirmed%20that%20the%20vessel%20sustained%20damage%2C%20suggesting%20a%20deliberate%20attack.%20The%20engine%20room%20was%20specifically%20targeted.%20The%20British%20security%20firm%20Ambrey%20reported%20that%20the%20incident%20occurred%20approximately%2067.7%20nautical%20miles%20southwest%20of%20Yemen's%20port%20of%20Hodeidah.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fmerchant-ship-hit-by-small-vessel-in-red-sea-ukmto-says%2Farticleshow%2F110939901.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fmerchant-ship-hit-by-small-vessel-in-red-sea-ukmto-says%2Famp_articleshow%2F110939901.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fmerchant-ship-hit-by-small-vessel-in-red-sea-ukmto-says%2Famp_articleshow%2F110939901.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mangalyaan-2%20On%20Mind%2C%20Indian%20Scientists%20Name%20Craters%20On%20Mars%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EScientists%20from%20the%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20(ISRO)%20have%20been%20able%20to%20get%20some%20craters%20named%20on%20planet%20Mars%20with%20Indian%20antecedents.%C2%A0All%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20bring%20back%20happy%20memories%20of%20India's%20maiden%20outing%20to%20Mars%20using%20the%20robotic%20satellite%20Mangalyaan%20and%20scientists%20are%20hoping%20that%20sooner%20than%20later%20the%20government%20may%20clear%20India's%20next%20mission%20to%20Mars%20through%2C%20Mangalyaan-2%2C%20which%20could%20include%20a%20soft%20landing%20on%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20crater%20has%20been%20named%20'Lal'%20on%20the%20Red%20Planet%20and%20it%20is%20named%20after%20the%20legendary%20Indian%20physicist%20Professor%20Devendra%20Lal%20who%20headed%20the%20cradle%20of%20ISRO%2C%20the%20Physical%20Research%20Laboratory%20(PRL)%20in%20Ahmedabad.%20Professor%20Lal%20spearheaded%20PRL%20from%201972-1983.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20a%20cosmic%20ray%20physicist%20who%20also%20loved%20chemistry.%20He%20later%20moved%20to%20the%20Scripps%20Institution%20of%20Oceanography%2C%20San%20Diego%2C%20California.%20A%20crater%20in%20the%20southern%20hemisphere%20of%20Mars%20with%20a%20diameter%20of%2069%20kilometres%20has%20been%20named%20'Lal'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ISRO%20team%20published%20the%20work%20of%20the%20discovery%20of%20the%20craters%20and%20its%20significance%20in%20a%20scientific%20journal%20named%20ICARUS%20and%20they%20say%20the%20scientific%20importance%20of%20this%20finding%20is%20that%20it%20also%20confirms%20that%20Mars%20was%20once%20wet%20and%20water%20has%20flown%20on%20the%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20small%20superimposed%20craters%2C%20on%20either%20side%20of%20Lal%20Crater%2C%20named%20as%20Mursan%20and%20Hilsa%2C%20provide%20the%20timeline%20for%20the%20infilling%20process%20of%20the%20Lal%20Crater%20and%20suggest%20that%20the%20infilling%20has%20been%20episodic.%20Also%2C%20this%20discovery%20provides%20compelling%20evidence%20that%20the%20water%20has%20moved%20large%20volumes%20of%20sediment%20into%20the%20crater%20now%20named%20as%20%26quot%3BLal%20Crater%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fnkb5von8_crater_625x300_12_June_24.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20craters%20are%20situated%20in%20the%20Tharsis%20volcanic%20region%20on%20Mars.%20On%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20PRL%2C%20the%20International%20Astronomical%20Union%20(IAU)%20Working%20Group%20for%20Planetary%20System%20Nomenclature%20approved%20naming%20the%20three%20craters%20on%20Mars'%20says%20a%20statement%20by%20PRL.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20crater%20has%20been%20named%20'Mursan'%20which%20is%20approximately%20a%2010%20km%20wide%20crater%20and%20superimposed%20on%20the%20eastern%20side%20of%20the%20rim%20of%20the%20Lal%20crater.%20It%20is%20named%20after%20a%20town%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMursan%20is%20a%20small%20with%20a%20population%20of%2011%2C500%20as%20per%20the%20latest%20census.%20It's%20located%20about%20200%20kilometres%20from%20Delhi%20in%20the%20district%20of%20Hathras%20(now%20named%20Mahamaya%20Nagar%20District)%20in%20UP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20name%20Mursan%20had%20been%20chosen%20since%20it%20is%20the%20birthplace%20of%20the%20current%20director%20of%20PRL%2C%20Dr%20Anil%20Bharadwaj%2C%20who%20is%20a%20recognised%20planetary%20scientist.%20%26quot%3BSmall%20craters%20on%20Mars%20can%20only%20be%20named%20after%20small%20towns%2C%20hence%20the%20team%20zeroed%20in%20Mursan%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Mr%20Bharadwaj%2C%20adding%20that%20his%20Indian%20passport%20proudly%20carries%20Mursan%20as%20his%20birthplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20crater%20to%20be%20named%20recently%20is%20called%20%26quot%3BHilsa%26quot%3B%2C%20it%20is%20also%20approximately%2010%20km%20wide%20and%20superimposed%20on%20the%20western%20side%20of%20the%20rim%20of%20the%20Lal%20crater.%20It%20is%20named%20after%20a%20town%20in%20Bihar.%20Incidentally%2C%20Hilsa%20is%20the%20birthplace%20of%20Dr%20Rajeev%20Ranjan%20Bharti%2C%20a%20scientist%20at%20PRL%20and%20the%20person%20who%20is%20part%20of%20the%20team%20that%20discovered%20these%20new%20craters%20on%20the%20Red%20Planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20launched%20its%20highly%20successful%20maiden%20mission%20to%20Mars%20named%20Mangalyaan%20in%202013%20and%20even%20before%20it%20reached%20the%20Red%20Planet%2C%20there%20were%20some%20craters%20with%20Indian%20names%20like%20the%20'Lonar'%20crater.%20Lonar%2C%2011.3%20km%20in%20diameter%2C%20is%20possibly%20named%20after%20Maharashtra's%20scenic%20town%20which%20was%20formed%20after%20an%20asteroid%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20crater%20'Poona'%20is%2020%20km%20in%20diameter%20and%20is%20named%20after%20the%20modern-day%20Pune%20city%20in%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20another%20crater%2C%20'Kakori'%2C%20has%20possibly%20derived%20its%20name%20from%20a%20town%20near%20Lucknow%20which%20shot%20to%20fame%20during%20the%20Independence%20movement.%20More%20recently%20another%20crater%20'Ramanathan%20Crater'%20was%20named%20after%20the%20first%20director%20of%20PRL.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20could%20well%20be%20visiting%20Mars%20again%2C%20Mr%20Bharadwaj%20says%20'Mangalyaan-2'%20is%20at%20a%20conceptual%20stage%20and%20design%20work%20is%20going%20on%20at%20ISRO.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20be%20a%20follow-up%20mission%20to%20the%20maiden%20'Mars%20Orbiter%20Mission'%20(MOM)%20and%20could%20include%20a%20soft%20landing%20with%20an%20Indian%20rover%20thrown%20for%20good%20measure%20and%20ideas%20on%20sending%20a%20helicopter%20are%20also%20being%20considered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSoft%20landing%20on%20Mars%20is%20tougher%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Mr%20Bharadwaj.%20He%20explains%20that%20Mars%20has%20a%20thin%20atmosphere%20and%20this%20causes%20heating%20of%20the%20spacecraft%2C%20but%20important%20lessons%20have%20been%20learnt%20from%20the%20successful%20soft%20landing%20of%20Chandrayaan-3%20and%20teams%20are%20working%20on%20all%20leads.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20scientists%20want%20to%20explore%20the%20Red%20Planet%20more%20intensively%20with%20the%20hope%20that%20like%20Chandrayaan-1%20made%20the%20epochal%20finding%20of%20the%20presence%20of%20water%20molecules%20on%20the%20parched%20surface%20of%20Moon%2C%20completely%20changing%20the%20geological%20understanding%20of%20our%20nearest%20celestial%20neighbour%2C%20Mangalyaan-2%20may%20provide%20clinching%20evidence%20of%20the%20presence%20of%20water%20on%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718188920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-10%2Frnuf0b08_mangalyaan_625x300_02_October_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fmangalyaan-2-on-mind-indian-scientists-name-craters-on-mars-5873775%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Scientists%20from%20the%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20(ISRO)%20have%20been%20able%20get%20some%20craters%20named%20on%20planet%20Mars%20with%20Indian%20antecedents.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fmangalyaan-2-on-mind-indian-scientists-name-craters-on-mars-5873775%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fmangalyaan-2-on-mind-indian-scientists-name-craters-on-mars-5873775%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fmangalyaan-2-on-mind-indian-scientists-name-craters-on-mars-5873775%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22PLI%20scheme%20to%20draw%20Rs%203-4%20trn%20investments%20over%204%20yrs%3B%20boost%20pvt%20capex%3A%20ICRA%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A17